# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Terraform — generated by `terraform init`, never commit these
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Provider binaries downloaded by `terraform init` (~100 MB for azurerm).
# Each developer runs `terraform init` to download them locally.
terraform/.terraform/

# Lock file that pins exact provider versions.
# Regenerated automatically on `terraform init`.
terraform/.terraform.lock.hcl

# State files contain the full picture of every resource Terraform manages,
# including sensitive values (kubeconfig, keys, IPs) in plain text.
# Committing state would expose credentials and cause conflicts between users.
# In a team/production setup, store state remotely (Azure Storage, Terraform Cloud).
terraform/terraform.tfstate
terraform/terraform.tfstate.backup

# Variable overrides — the user creates this from terraform.tfvars.example
# and fills in their own subscription_id. Never commit real values.
terraform/terraform.tfvars
